HB 1006 Original 2026 Regular Session Wilford Carter
Abstract: Extends time period to file an opposition to a motion for summary judgment.
Present law requires any opposition to a motion for summary judgment and all documents
in support of the opposition be filed and served in accordance with present law not less than
15 days prior to the hearing on the motion.
Proposed law changes the time delay to file an opposition from 15 days to 10 days prior to
the hearing on the motion.
(Amends C.C.P. Art. 966(B)(2))
